sys_hub_action_type_definition.description:
Moves the items that are owned by a user to a target location, typically used in case of user deprovisioning where you need to transfer the ownership of files by moving it to a common folder managed by a Service account.

Inputs:

  • Source User ID - The ID of the user whose owned content will be moved.
  • Destination User ID - The ID of the user who the folder will be transferred to.

Outputs:

  • Status - Will be set to "Success" if the request succeeds or "Error" if a failure occurs.
  • Error Message - Will be populated when the status is "Error".
  • Folder ID - ID of the new folder where all items have been moved.
  • Folder Info - Information of the created folder in JSON format. Will be populated in case of success.
  • Moved Owned Item - ID of the new folder where all items have been moved.
    • ID.
    • Description.
    • Type.
    • E Tag.
    • Item Status.
    • Name.
    • Size.
    • Expires AT.

Error Messages:

  • Invalid source user ID.
  • Cannot transfer to user who is not in the enterprise.
  • Cannot transfer from user who is not in the enterprise.
  • Invalid username or password/token.
  • The credentials associated with the Box Spoke connection does not have enough permission to perform this action.

To use this action, the corresponding Box connection and credential must be created and associated with the Box Connection & Credential alias. Learn More

Note: Requires a subscription for production use. Read More.
